# Magpie plugin bundle — ed25519 signing public key
#
# Algorithm: ed25519. The value below is the raw 32-byte public key,
# lowercase hex (64 chars).
#
# The matching PRIVATE key is held only as the GitHub Actions repo secret
# `MAGPIE_PLUGIN_SIGNING_KEY` (an openssl ed25519 PEM), used by the
# `release` job in .github/workflows/release.yml to sign
# magpie-plugin-v<version>.tar.gz — the signature is published as the
# magpie-plugin-v<version>.tar.gz.sig sidecar on each GitHub Release (raw
# 64-byte ed25519 signature over the exact bundle bytes, hex-encoded).
#
# This file is committed for transparency/reference only — it is NOT the
# trust root bamboo actually uses. bamboo ships this same key baked into
# its default trusted-publishers store (`plugin_trust.trusted_keys`), so
# installing an official signed Magpie release needs no extra flags.
# Publishing it here just lets anyone cross-check "the key bamboo trusts
# for magpie" against what this repo's own release pipeline signs with.

47e971c39cd93adb18cff50e097cb387df49e9c4d33b0ed62f693eabbe7fc66e
